 generated helper classes. \\n\\nI need to configure the Gradle JaCoCoReport tasks properly to address this, possibly importing specific plugins or using the correct naming. It's a bit of a maze!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Adjusting JaCoCo Tasks**\\n\\nI'm figuring out how to adjust my Gradle tasks. After the compile tasks, I can specify that `jacocoTestReport` depends on `generateDirectAccessClass` and add the `generatedDirectAccessClasses` to `classDirectories`. \\n\\nHowever, I’m realizing I only need this `classDirectories` property for the JaCoCo report, and dynamic Groovy should be okay. I’m a bit concerned that adding all generated classes might cause issues with duplicates, especially if they match existing class names. It’s a bit tricky!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_UVNBVOwFYZjtCSQK4SMLDx8k|fc_004d18f7b8d03fa5016a01ca414c94819f91f3b13ccdd66b14", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/io.rest-assured/rest-assured/5.5.0/build.gradle", "edits": [{"oldText": "sourceSets {\n    test {\n        output.dir(generatedDirectAccessClasses, builtBy: generateDirectAccessClass)\n    }\n}\n\n tasks.named(\"compileTestJava\") {", "newText": "sourceSets {\n    test {\n        output.dir(generatedDirectAccessClasses, builtBy: generateDirectAccessClass)\n    }\n}\n\nClosure<Void> patchEffectiveJacocoClass = { String classEntryName ->\n    String effectiveJarDirectoryName = \"rest_assured_${libraryVersion.replaceAll('[^A-Za-z0-9]', '_')}_jar\"\n    File sourceFile = generatedDirectAccessClasses.get().file(classEntryName).asFile\n    File effectiveFile = layout.buildDirectory\n            .file(\"jacoco/effective/${effectiveJarDirectoryName}/${classEntryName}\")\n            .get()\n            .asFile\n    if (sourceFile.exists()) {\n        effectiveFile.parentFile.mkdirs()\n        effectiveFile.bytes = sourceFile.bytes\n    }\n    null\n}\n\nClosure<Void> patchTrustAndKeystoreCreateStoreClosureForJacoco = {\n    patchEffectiveJacocoClass(\"io/restassured/internal/TrustAndKeystoreSpecImpl\\$_createStore_closure1.class\")\n    null\n}\n\ntasks.matching { Task task ->\n    task.name == \"jacocoTestReport\"\n}.configureEach { Task task ->\n    task.dependsOn(generateDirectAccessClass)\n    task.doFirst {\n        patchTrustAndKeystoreCreateStoreClosureForJacoco()\n    }\n}\n\ntasks.named(\"test\") {\n    dependsOn(generateDirectAccessClass)\n    doFirst {\n        patchTrustAndKeystoreCreateStoreClosureForJacoco()\n    }\n    doLast {\n        patchTrustAndKeystoreCreateStoreClosureForJacoco()\n    }\n}\n\ntasks.named(\"compileTestJava\") {"}]}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 591, "output": 1975, "cacheRead": 77312, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 79878, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778502185862, "responseId": "resp_004d18f7b8d03fa5016a01ca2a7250819f93ccb3394c59248e"}}
